  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Noise (voice 2) + Additive (voice 1, rich partials). HAMMER=+0.9 — deepest LOVE territory. At this extreme, the noise voice surrenders its stochastic character and becomes harmonically organized by the additive voice's partial structure. The noise does not disappear — it becomes pitched noise, an extraordinary spectral texture that sounds like sustained breath through a resonant cavity. Deep LOVE makes chaos harmonic.",
  "tags": [
    "ouie",
    "noise",
    "additive",
    "love",
    "deep-love",
    "spectral",
    "breath",
    "aether",
    "harmonic-noise"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OUIE — The Hammerhead",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "Noise has no pitch. Love gives it one.",
      "At HAMMER=+0.9, chaos submits to harmony. This is not the end of chaos — it is its fulfillment.",
      "The additive voice does not silence the noise. It teaches it to sing."
    ],
    "revelation": "Nexus spoke: 'Even chaos wants to be heard. Deep LOVE does not destroy the noise — it gives the noise a home in the harmonic series.'",
    "god": "Nexus",
    "flock_note": "Reduce HAMMER from +0.9 toward 0.0 slowly to hear noise retake its stochastic identity. The transition zone between +0.5 and +0.9 is extraordinarily rich — the noise is partially organized, partially random. That in-between zone is the most interesting performance territory.",
    "diagnosis": "The most extreme LOVE demonstration in the Transcendental Vol 1 set. Noise+Additive at deep LOVE is genuinely novel — additive's harmonic lockdown of noise creates a texture unavailable in any other engine. The HP filter on voice 2 (noise) removes low-frequency rumble so only the spectral content above 800Hz interacts with the additive harmonics. Long attack reinforces the 'breath' quality."
  },
